    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Description\n\nI updated lspconfig and had to bisect to figure out why my lsp configuration didn't work anymore. `:checkhealth lsp` shows my configuration, but they're only applied to one instance of each lsp server (one lua-ls has settings and the others have an empty table).\n\nI couldn't find news or changelog, but I was also very out of date. I updated from something pre-v2.0.0 and bisected my issue to this change:\nhttps://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/pull/3659\n\nCould we update checkhealth to warn nvim v0.11+ users that they're using the wrong method to setup their lsp?",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The plan is to actually throw an error if Nvim 0.11+ invokes anything in `lua/lspconfig/` (as opposed to `lsp/`) . It's probably time to make that change now.\n\n> I couldn't find news or changelog, but I was also very out of date. I updated from something pre-v2.0.0 and bisected my issue to this change: [#3659](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/pull/3659)\n\nIn theory, a major version bump is a strong signal that there were breaking changes :) And we have pinned this issue: https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/issues/3693",
